<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="014" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Backfill sprk_playbookcode on 6 production-bound playbooks (Dataverse data update)</title>
    <phase>1: §1.7 Stable Codes Migration</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>013</dependencies>
    <blocks>015</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, data, migration</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Dataverse data update (not schema); sequentially required because all 6 updates target the same entity; STANDARD per Step 0.5 — not a code change but production-data write</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>1-C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Same Dataverse entity (`sprk_analysisplaybook`); serialized to avoid optimistic concurrency conflicts and to keep the 6-update audit trail in one batch.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Backfill the `sprk_playbookcode` alternate-key column on the 6 production-bound playbooks per spec §1.5 + §1.7.3 codes table. Use the `Update-Playbook.ps1` script or Dataverse MCP `update_record` tool. Do NOT modify any other field — name, GUID, output schema must remain unchanged per NFR-02. After backfill, verify each playbook resolves via `GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/{code}`.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE Dataverse data-migration specialist. Expert in PAC CLI + Dataverse Web API + MCP tools for record updates.</role>

  <goal>
    The 6 production-bound playbooks each have a populated `sprk_playbookcode` matching spec §1.7.3 codes table:
    1. `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` → `sprk_playbookcode = "summarize-document-chat"`
    2. `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1` → `"summarize-document-workspace"`
    3. `"Summarize New File(s)"` → `"summarize-new-files"`
    4. `"Document Profile"` → `"document-profile"`
    5. `"Create New Matter Pre-Fill"` → `"create-matter-prefill"`
    6. `"Create New Project Pre-Fill"` → `"create-project-prefill"`
    Verification via `GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/{code}` returns 200 for each.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec §1.5 + §1.7.3 + NFR-02. `sprk_playbookcode` already exists as `NVARCHAR(10)` alternate key per Dataverse describe (see CLAUDE.md project-specific MUSTs). This task only POPULATES it on the 6 production-bound playbooks — no schema change, no playbook output/name change. Without this backfill, task 015 (`SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` migration) cannot resolve `summarize-document-chat` and the entire wave 1-D blocks.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/Update-Playbook.ps1</file>
      <file>docs/data-model/sprk_analysisplaybook.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-002">Dataverse data writes go through Web API / SDK / MCP; no direct SQL.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">No PII or memory content in update payload — these are administrative code values only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-02 binding: production-bound playbook NAME, GUID, output schema unchanged. ONLY `sprk_playbookcode` is written.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Verify `sprk_playbookcode` is empty (or wrong) on each of the 6 BEFORE writing; do not blindly overwrite if a different value is already in place.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Run against DEV environment first; document evidence; ONLY after Phase 1 deploy (task 026) run against higher environments via separate operator action.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Code value must be tenant-scoped uniqueness if multiple tenants share Dataverse — confirm via the unresolved-questions item in spec.md "Tenant scope confirmation".</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-002-dataverse-data-access.md</file>
      <file>docs/data-model/sprk_analysisplaybook.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Use Dataverse MCP `read_query` (or PAC CLI) to fetch the 6 production-bound playbooks by name. Record their `sprk_analysisplaybookid` GUIDs + current `sprk_playbookcode` values.</step>
    <step order="2">If any of the 6 already has a non-empty `sprk_playbookcode` that differs from the spec §1.7.3 target — STOP, document in `notes/debug/014-playbookcode-conflict.md`, escalate to owner.</step>
    <step order="3">Resolve the unresolved-question on tenant-uniqueness — query rows in current tenant to confirm none of the 6 target codes already used by a different playbook. Document in handoff note.</step>
    <step order="4">Build the update payload — 6 records, each `{ sprk_analysisplaybookid: &lt;GUID&gt;, sprk_playbookcode: &lt;code&gt; }`.</step>
    <step order="5">Execute updates via Dataverse MCP `update_record` (one call per playbook) or `Update-Playbook.ps1`. Capture response evidence.</step>
    <step order="6">Verify each update via `read_query`: `SELECT sprk_name, sprk_playbookcode FROM sprk_analysisplaybook WHERE sprk_analysisplaybookid IN (...)`.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify via API: `curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" "$BFF_URL/api/ai/playbooks/by-code/summarize-document-chat"` (and other 5 codes); each returns 200.</step>
    <step order="8">Write handoff note `notes/handoffs/014-playbookcode-backfill-evidence.md` with: pre-state, post-state, verification results, environment.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 014 → ✅. current-task.md → ready for task 015.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Update-Playbook.ps1 + sprk_analysisplaybook data model doc</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">PAC CLI or curl to verify API resolution</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Handoff note + (if conflict) debug note</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Update TASK-INDEX.md</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="data">sprk_analysisplaybook records 1–6 have populated sprk_playbookcode per spec §1.7.3</output>
    <output type="docs">notes/handoffs/014-playbookcode-backfill-evidence.md — pre/post values + API verification</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">All 6 production-bound playbooks have non-empty `sprk_playbookcode` matching spec §1.7.3 codes table.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No playbook NAME, GUID, or output schema modified (verified via `read_query` diff of name + JPS fields pre/post).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/summarize-document-chat` returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/summarize-document-workspace` returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/summarize-new-files` returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/document-profile` returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/create-matter-prefill` returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`GET /api/ai/playbooks/by-code/create-project-prefill` returns 200.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Handoff note documents pre + post state + environment.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    DEV environment ONLY in this task. Higher-environment promotion is owned by Phase 1 deploy (task 026) — DO NOT run against staging/prod from this task. If tenant-uniqueness check fails (code collision), pivot to documenting the conflict and stop — do NOT invent a workaround.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    <skill>.claude/skills/task-execute/SKILL.md</skill>
    <protocol>STANDARD rigor protocol — Dataverse data update with verification gates; code-review skipped at Step 9.5 (no code change).</protocol>
  </execution>
</task>
